Class ShannonsGraphicPanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • network.ShannonsGraphicPanel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.Observer, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class ShannonsGraphicPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements java.util.Observer
    Program Description: Program will display a G.U.I for the user to input the bandwidth, and signalToNoise ratio. User has the option of either inputing the amounts manually through the keyboard, or using the sliders to adjust the values. When the user interacts with the text box of the sliders, this will adjust the graph at the bottom of the window, relative to their values.
    Version:
    1.0.0 Date 2015/11/04 Assignment: Lab Assignment 3 - Shannons Theorem (MVC) ShannonsGraphicsPanel class is part of the view for the (MVC). ShannonsGraphicsPanel will outline the graphics view that controls the values of bandwidth, signal to noise, and max data rate graph. ShannonsGraphicsPanel extends JPanel to implement panel methods and attributes. ShannonsGraphicsPanel implements Observer to update the graph values.
    Author:
    Ruchika Chona
